%N A366193 For n >= 0, a(n) is the least x >= 0 such that x^2 + (x + 2*n)^2 + 1 = p, p prime number (A000040).
%C A366193 For a(n) = 0 the resulting primes p >= 5 see in A002496.
%H A366193 Stoyan I. Dimitrov, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2011.03967">A ternary diophantine inequality by primes with one of the form p = x^2 + y^2 + 1</a>, arXiv:2011.03967 [math.NT], 2020.
%F A366193 a(n) = 0 for n from A001912.
%e A366193 n = 0: x^2 + x^2 + 1 = p is valid for the least x = 1, p = 3, thus a(0) = 1.
%e A366193 n = 6: x^2 + (x + 12)^2 + 1 = p is valid for the least x = 9, p = 523, thus a(6) = 9.
%o A366193 (PARI) a(n) = my(x=0); while (!isprime(x^2 + (x + 2*n)^2 + 1), x++); x; \\ _Michel Marcus_, Oct 03 2023
